OMTO3d product is made available from the GES DISC ( http://mirador.gsfc.nasa.gov/) for the public access. The documents giving the details of data filtering and the data read and visualization software are also made available from the GES DISC site: http://disc.gsfc.nasa.gov/Aura/OMI/omto3d_v003.shtml .  (The shortname for this Level-3 TOMS-Like total column ozone product is OMTO3d_V003)   There are two Aura/OMI daily global TOMS-Like Total Column Ozone gridded products, OMTO3e is gridded in 0.25x0.25 degree, and OMTO3d is gridded in 1x1 degree.</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>aerosols</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>atmosphere</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>atmospheric-chemistry</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>clouds</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>earth-science</dcat:keyword>     <foaf:homepage rdf:resource="https://catalog.data.gov/dataset/omi-aura-toms-like-ozone-aerosol-index-cloud-radiance-fraction-daily-l3-global-1-0x1-0-deg"></foaf:homepage>     <rdfs:label>omi-aura-toms-like-ozone-aerosol-index-cloud-radiance-fraction-daily-l3-global-1-0x1-0-deg</rdfs:label>     <dct:identifier>omi-aura-toms-like-ozone-aerosol-index-cloud-radiance-fraction-daily-l3-global-1-0x1-0-deg</dct:identifier>     <dct:title>OMI/Aura TOMS-Like Ozone, Aerosol Index, Cloud Radiance Fraction Daily L3 Global 1.0x1.0 deg V003</dct:title>         <dcat:distribution>             <dcat:Distribution>                 <dcat:accessURL rdf:resource="http://reverb.echo.nasa.gov/reverb?selected=C188290546-GSFCS4PA"></dcat:accessURL>                     <dct:format>                         <dct:IMT>                             <rdf:value>HTML</rdf:value>                             <rdfs:label>HTML</rdfs:label>                         </dct:IMT>                     </dct:format>                <dct:title>Web Page</dct:title>             </dcat:Distribution>         </dcat:distribution>     <dct:contributor>       <rdf:Description>         <foaf:name>JENNIFER WEI, PH.
